KAPPA CLIMBS

A card book featuring a rambunctious kappa girl, designed for toddler to give them a preview into what happens if they climb too high.

The Kappa is a Japanese spirit that looks like a duck and has water in the top of its head they should never spill. The water is commonly surrounded by hair.

Kappa Climb…

Kappa get hurt

I used these concepts to design this character, her head is a flower where the centre is water.

I thought the idea of teaching toddlers to protecting their head connected well with the idea of kappa’s water.

The book follows a formula of “Kappa climbs ____” “Kappa gets hurt” with the last page being different

“Kappa climbs papa”

“Kappa gets a hug!”

Book Dummy Available on request

Perrywinkle

After I had my daughter I would draw cute characters for her to make her happy and I was inspired to make my 1st book for her because she loves reading. The book follows the structure of Billy Goats Gruff but is set in the ocean with sea creatures.

The main character is a snail named Perrywinkle after the real world breed of snail.

The 3 character each have unique defences against the eel and perrkywinkle seems the most harmless compared to a jellyfish and a crab.

It touches on the concept of “a good defence is a good offence” and you don’t need to be scary or big to be tough.

draft

In the original story there had 2 snails perrywinkle and Spike but it seemed unbalanced so spike was replaced with crab called Snip

Draft Copy Available on request
